- Added runtime orbit debug logging controls. Admins can now toggle orbit (and osqueryd) verbose logging without restarting orbit, either team-wide via `agent_options.orbit.debug_logging` or for a single host via the **Enable debug logging** host action, a new banner + indicator pill on the host details page, the `POST /api/v1/fleet/hosts/{id}/debug-logging` endpoint, or `fleetctl hosts debug-logging --host <id> --enable [--duration 1h]`. Host-level overrides auto-expire (default 24h, max 7d). See `docs/Contributing/architecture/orbit-debug-logging.md`.
- Fixed orbit's command-line flags reconciliation so it now clears osquery flags on disk when the server stops pushing them. Previously, once flags had been written to `osquery.flags`, removing the matching `command_line_flags` entry from agent options (or turning off debug logging) left osqueryd stuck with the old flags until orbit was manually restarted.
